'''Amalthea''' may refer to: *[[Amalthea (mythology)]], the foster-mother of Zeus in Greek mythology *[[Amalthea (moon)]], a moon of Jupiter *[[Amalthea (technical summit)]], an event of IIT Gandhinagar *[[MV Amalthea|MV ''Amalthea'']], a cargo ship *[[113 Amalthea]], a main-belt asteroid *[[Amalthea Cellars]], a winery in New Jersey *[[Cumaean Sibyl]] or Amalthea, a priestess presiding over the Apollonian oracle at Cumae, a Greek colony near Naples, Italy *''Amalthea'', a ship bombed by [[Anton Nilson]] in 1908 *Lady Amalthea, a character in ''[[The Last Unicorn]]''
